\begin_layout Subsection*
The Abstract
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Access to ultra-short laser pulses that last long enough to accommodate
 only a few optical cycles, is beginning to allow time dependent nuclear
 and electron dynamics to be probed within atoms and molecules, thereby
 enhancing our ability to gain proper insights into how quantum systems
 react to strong external fields and how they might be subjected to optical
 control.
 In this talk I shall present an overview of how we have utilized intense
 laser pulses of duration as short as 4 femto seconds to explore dynamical
 effects of relevance to diverge areas of the natural and engineering sciences,
 including application pertaining to DNA damage, laser-induced materials
 modification and green photonics.
\end_layout

